# Web vs App Landing + Footer Completion

When asked to fix landing/footer navigation:

1. Ensure every visible footer link resolves to an existing route/page.
2. Create missing pages with production-appropriate placeholder content (not dead links).
3. Keep web landing (`/home`) and native-app landing distinct when requested.
4. Prefer a simpler swipe/Tinder-style app landing for native contexts.
5. Standardize support email references to requested canonical address.
6. Verify by:
   - route map check,
   - lint/build checks,
   - manual path sanity list in runbook/docs.

Do not leave "coming soon" links without a route. If a page is intentionally minimal, it must still be complete enough for App Review context.
